<seg id=1> The Minister of Cote d'Ivoire's Treasury and Economic Department said that economy in West Africa is remarkably recovering and growing </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> Xinhua News agency, Abidjan, January 18th, by Daocheng Linhu- The Minister of Cote d'Ivoire's Treasury and Economic Department Enkena said on January 17th that, the economy in West Africa and the countries that are members of the Currency Coalition is remarkably recovering and growing. The major economic elements are in good condition. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=3> At the economists' meeting held by the French - Cote d'Ivoire Business Club, Enkena said that, in West Africa and the countries that are members of the Currency Coalition, the average annual economic growth has been recovering increasing by 5.9% in 1996 and reaching 6.3% in 1997. However, the average annual economic growth was only 2.6% in 1994. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=4> He said that, the countries in West Africa have vigorously improved the previously unbalanced conditions of imports and exports and public investments. As a result, the favorable balance of trade increased on a big scale; Meanwhile, the budget deficit was reduced remarkably, accounting for only 1.3% of the gross domestic product of each country. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=5> While talking about the possible impacts the European countries movie to use one single currency might have on African currency, Enkena said that, people should not worry about the future of African currency. </seg>
<seg id=6> Because the economies in West Africa and in the countries of the Currency Coalition are recovering remarkably, he said that, in the near future, there will not be any huge depreciation in African currency like the one where the currency depreciation reached 50% in January, 1994. </seg>
</p>
